{{Infobox person | name = Guido Ruggiero | image = | alt = | caption = | birth_date = <!-- {{Birth date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | birth_place = [[Danbury, Connecticut]] | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) --> | death_place = | known_for = | education = M.A., Ph.D. | alma_mater = [[University of Colorado at Boulder|University of Colorado]], [[UCLA]] | occupation = [[microhistory|Microhistorian]], professor }} '''Guido Ruggiero''' is a notable [[microhistory|microhistorian]] and professor and chair of the [[University of Miami]] History Department.<ref>[http://www.as.miami.edu/history/people/faculty/guido-ruggiero/ University of Miami faculty page]</ref><ref>[http://www.gf.org/fellows/12687-guido-ruggiero Guggenheim Foundation page]</ref> His most notable work is ''Binding Passions: Tales of Magic, Marriage and Power from the End of the Renaissance''.
