[[File:Smith's Bible Dictionary 1863.jpg|thumb|<center>''[[Smith's Bible Dictionary]]'' 1863]] [[File:Easton's Bible Dictionary 1894.jpg|thumb|<center>''[[Easton's Bible Dictionary]]'' 1894]] [[File:Nave's Topical Bible 1905.jpg|thumb|<center>[[Nave's Topical Bible]] 1905]] This page introduces a list of [[proper noun|proper names]] from the [[Bible]].
Some of the names are given with a proposed etymological meaning. For further information on the names included on the list, the reader may consult the sources listed below in the References and External Links.
==Significance of names==
Names play a variety of roles in the Bible. The names sometimes relate to the role of those characters in biblical narratives, as in the case of Nabal, a foolish man whose name means "fool."<ref>See 1 Samuel 25:25</ref> Names in the Bible can represent human hopes, divine revelations, or are used by prophets to illustrate their prophecies. See also [[Theophory]].<ref>Lockyer, pp. 11-14</ref>
